{"word":"εὐώνυμος","slug":"εὐώνυμος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b><el>εὐώνυμος, ον</el></b> [<el><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:εὖ\">εὖ</a>, <a class=\"S\" href=\"S:ὄνομα\">ὄνομα</a></el>; ‘having an auspicious name’: a euphemistic term for the ‘left’ position because bad omens came from the left] <b>left,</b> in distinction <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ fr.\">fr.</a> ‘right’ (<a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ cp.\">cp.</a> <el>ἀρίστερος</el>) <b><a href='B:470 20:21'>Mt 20:21</a>; <a href='B:470 25:33'>25:33</a>; <a href='B:470 27:38'>27:38</a>; <a href='B:480 10:40'>Mk 10:40</a>; <a href='B:510 21:3'>Ac 21:3</a>; <a href='B:730 10:2'>Rv 10:2</a>.</b> <center id=\"nav_bottom\"> <a id=\"left_arrow\" href=\"S:εὐωδία\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> <a id=\"bottom_home\" href=\"S:#1.Table of Contents\">&emsp;&emsp;</a> <a id=\"right_arrow\" href=\"S:εὐωχία\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> </center> "}]}